					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4405707#post-3644573</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4405707/a-real-humdinger#post-3644573</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 03 Dec 2017 02:29:03 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>2788421</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>“Did I ever tell you that Stretchy and Masky were supposed to be the first of my own knock-off line of Little Misters? They were originally Mr. Stretch and Mr. Mask, but then this rock’em sock’em robot shows up to the Circus screaming ‘LITTLE MISTERS IS THE INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY OF DOCTOR WONDERTAINMENT’, so I had to ease off.”</p> </blockquote> <p>I can't believe you used this idea, and I'm loving it. The dialogue between Fuller and Tom was fun, and that ending was the funniest I had read in a long time.</p> <p>Upvoted, pls give me moar</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
